{
  "texts": [
    "Let d = 1, P = P X ⊗ δ 0, such that the \"sampling distribution\" P X is supported on [0, 1] such that, if X ∼ P X, has mean and variance 1/2.",
    "Assumption 1 is non-vacuous, with a simple example establishing existence being a standard fair Bernoulli trial.",
    "Though, naturally, there is a plethora of more involved examples one can easily construct by dabbling.Example 1 (Bernoulli Trial).",
    "Any fair Bernoulli trial P X (X = 1) = P X (X = 0) = 1/2 satisfies Assumption 1.",
    "Moreover, ξ def.= 2X -2 is a Rademacher random variable (random sign)."
  ]
}